ng torus, while driving a fast bi-polar wind. These results therefore\nprovide strong supporting evidence for the hypothesis that the formation\nmechanism for high-mass stars is qualitatively similar to that of low-mass\nstars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Nov 2009 10:23:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-14"}
