radiation. Oxygen vacancies are deep donors in ZnO, but\nsurely they influence the stability of the shallow donors (presumably zinc\ninterstitial related) and vice versa. This is in conformity with recent\ntheoretical calculations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Nov 2009 12:29:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 22 Dec 2009 06:59:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-14"}
